rafts dating from the final 21 months of Günther’s life. During this time, Günther wrote new derisive verses, panegyrics, and wedding verses; spiritual poems for a devotional setting; and his well-known self-justification letter to his father. Despite illness and exhaustion, Günther was able to maintain his poetic sensibility, his role as learned poet, and his clever wit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGünther, Johann Christian, 1695-1723xCriticism and interpretation. . 4aEdition. 4aGelegenheitsgedicht. 4aGünther, Johann Christian. 4aSchuldrama. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / European / General.2bisacsh  aAcademic drama.  aEdition.  aJohann Christian Günther.  aOccasional poem.1 aBölhoff, Reiner, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW0 cEPUBz97831103838740 cprintz978311029521440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311034558240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110345582423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110345582/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLWb2014  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014